{"id":43637,"title":"Calculating Colony-forming Units","title_html":"<p>Calculating Colony-forming Units<\/p>","image":{"source":"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/public\/c24afd6f4869761fdccc715e916a6c94d0780fe97a6274f5f18372fe7b3b455d\/cp3fbenhp.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/public\/c24afd6f4869761fdccc715e916a6c94d0780fe97a6274f5f18372fe7b3b455d\/cp3fbenhp.png"},"doi":"dx.doi.org\/10.17504\/protocols.io.bnuvmew6","doi_status":2,"uri":"calculating-colony-forming-units-bnuvmew6","type_id":4,"template_id":3,"published_on":1605884478,"parent_protocols":[],"parent_collections":[],"cited_protocols":[],"version_id":0,"version_data":{"id":"0","code":"bnuvmew6","parent_id":0,"parent_uri":null,"is_same_owner":false,"has_pending_merge_request":false,"has_approved_merge_request":false},"created_on":1603458012,"modified_on":null,"categories":null,"public":1,"is_unlisted":0,"creator":{"name":"Bark Beetle Mycobiome Research Coordination Network ","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[{"affiliation":"","url":"","is_default":1}],"username":"bark-beetle-mycobiome-research-coordination-networ","note":null,"link":null,"image":{"source":"\/img\/avatars\/005.png","placeholder":"\/img\/avatars\/005.png"},"badges":[{"id":4,"image":{"source":"\/img\/badges\/gold.svg","placeholder":"\/img\/badges\/gold.svg"},"name":"Gold power author!"},{"id":6,"image":{"source":"\/img\/badges\/accelerator.svg","placeholder":"\/img\/badges\/accelerator.svg"},"name":"Science accelerator"}],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},"journal":null,"journal_name":null,"journal_link":null,"article_citation":null,"has_versions":0,"link":null,"total_collections":0,"number_of_steps":0,"authors":[{"name":"Jiri Hulcr","affiliation":"University of Florida","affiliations":[],"username":null,"note":null,"link":null,"image":{"source":null,"placeholder":null},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},{"name":"You Li","affiliation":"University of Florida","affiliations":[],"username":null,"note":null,"link":null,"image":{"source":null,"placeholder":null},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false}],"versions":[],"groups":[],"is_owner":1,"has_subprotocols":0,"is_subprotocol":0,"is_bookmarked":0,"can_claim_authorship":0,"can_accept_authorship":0,"can_be_copied":1,"can_remove_fork":1,"fork_id":null,"url":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/view\/calculating-colony-forming-units-bnuvmew6","forks_count":{"private":0,"public":0},"access":{"can_view":1,"can_remove":0,"can_add":0,"can_edit":0,"can_publish":0,"can_get_doi":0,"can_share":1,"can_move":1,"can_move_outside":1,"can_transfer":1,"can_download":1,"is_locked":0},"guid":"AE7A50F0152F11EB965E352B165C46E9","state_version_id":19,"steps":[],"document":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">To estimate the initial number of colony-forming units in a mycangium, use the technique of serial dilution when plating. After colonies grow, multiply the number of colonies on the plate by the inverse of the initial dilution factor.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ol style = \"list-style-type: decimal;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Prepare two tubes per each sample, label them \u201c0.1\u201d and \u201c0.01\u201d, fill each with 500 ul of water or PBS.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Suspend mycangium in the tube \u201c0.1\u201d and vortex.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\"><span>Plate <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">50 ul<\/span><span> of the suspension on media. Record the plate as \u201c0.1 dilution\u201d in [PLATES].[note] in the Isolations database.<\/span><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\"><span>Transfer <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">50 ul<\/span><span> of the initial suspension to the second tube (\u201c0.01\u201d) and vortex.<\/span><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\"><span>Plate <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">50 ul<\/span><span> of the second suspension on <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">second<\/span><span> media plate, and record that plate as \u201c0.01 dilution\u201d.<\/span><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\"><span>Plate <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">5 ul<\/span><span> of the second suspension on a <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">third<\/span><span> plate, and record it as \u201c0.001 dilution\u201d.<\/span><\/li><\/ol><\/div><\/div>","materials":[],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">This protocol describes how to estimate the number of colony-forming units.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>This protocol is part of the Bark Beetle Mycobiome (BBM) Research Coordination Network. For more information on the BBM international network: Hulcr J, Barnes I, De Beer ZW, Duong TA, Gazis R, Johnson AJ, Jusino MA, Kasson MT, Li Y, Lynch S, Mayers C, Musvuugwa T, Roets F, Seltmann KC, Six D, Vanderpool D, & Villari C. 2020. Bark beetle mycobiome: collaboratively defined research priorities on a widespread insect-fungus symbiosis. Symbiosis 81: 101\u2013113 <\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/doi.org\/10.1007\/s13199-020-00686-9\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\">https:\/\/doi.org\/10.1007\/s13199-020-00686-9<\/span><\/a><span>.<\/span><\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1605884478}